cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper deals with formalizing the semantics and termination of logic programs with dynamic scheduling, which is a topic closely related to programming languages and logic. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves formal logic and reasoning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses parallel programming, which could place it in cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper deals with input-consuming derivations, which could also relate to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
